<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4605902>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Fig. 3. — Distribution of Moringa hildebrandtii in Madagascar. M. hildebrandtii is commonly cultivated in the area delimited by a dashed line on the west coast. Previous authors have cited the light gray area between Morondava and Tulear as being the native range of the species. It is more likely the dark gray area in the extreme southwest; searches for the tree should concentrate there." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4605902/files/figure.png" .

